@database ColorfieldClass
@index "Classes.guide/Main"

@Node Main "RxMUI - Colorfield Class"


Colorfield class    @{"Index" link "Classes.guide/Main"} @{"Super" link "AreaClass.guide/Main"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  Colorfield class creates a rectangle filled with a specific
  color, useful e.g. within a palette requester. You can change
  the color of the field at any time by setting its RGB
  attributes.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}Blue@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A 4 bytes max long packet chars string ('bbbbbbbb'x) blue
  component. Values range from 0 (no blue) to $ffffffff (full
  blue).

  @{fg shine}Green@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A 4 bytes max long packet chars string ('bbbbbbbb'x) green
  component. Values range from 0 (no green) to $ffffffff (full
  green).

  @{fg shine}Pen@{fg text}
  N ISGN
  When specified, the colorfield uses exactly this pen instead of
  trying to obtain a new one.

  @{fg shine}Red@{fg text}
  M ISGN G2N
  A 4 bytes max long packet chars string ('bbbbbbbb'x) red
  component. Values range from 0 (no red) to $ffffffff (full
  red).

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  None defined

@EndNode
